<p>Megan Hyska, currently assistant professor of philosophy at <a href="https://philosophy.northwestern.edu/">Northwestern University</a>, will be moving to <a href="https://ahc.leeds.ac.uk/philosophy">University of Leeds</a>, where she will be associate professor of philosophy.<span id="more-56488"></span></p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="wp-image-56489 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-996x1024.png" alt="" width="400" height="411" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-996x1024.png 996w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-292x300.png 292w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-768x790.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-1024x1053.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan-400x411.png 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/hyska-megan.png 1070w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p><a href="https://www.meganhyska.com/">Dr Hyska</a>&#8216;s research is in social philosophy of language, social metaphysics, and social epistemology, focusing especially on questions about political communication. She has written on topics such as social organizing, social movements, propaganda, AI-generated media, the act of address, and the value of communication itself. You can learn more about her work <a href="https://www.meganhyska.com/copy-of-research">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/megan-hyska">here</a>.</p>
<p>She takes up her new position at Leeds in August, 2026.</p>
<p>(via Pekka Väyrynen)</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2026/02/06/hyska-from-northwestern-to-leeds/">Hyska from Northwestern to Leeds</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>